{
  "texts": [
    "the point where the combined population is reduced to the desired size.",
    "This selection process prioritizes individuals starting from the first Pareto front and moves sequentially to subsequent fronts.",
    "During selection, if the cumulative size of the chosen individuals, including the members of the current Pareto front, does not exceed the predefined population size, the entire Pareto front is incorporated into the selection pool.",
    "Otherwise, the ones with the best crowding distances in the current Pareto front are added to it.",
    "Crowding distance in NSGA-II is a measure used to maintain diversity within a population by determining how crowded an individual is compared to its neighbors in the input space [23]."
  ]
}